---
title: `$to::query()`
description: Convert PHP array into URL query string.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
To::query($in, $c = ['?', '&', '=', ""]);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$test = To::query([
    'a' => 1,
    'b' => true,
    'c' => 'true',
    'd' => false,
    'e' => 'false',
    'f' => null,
    'g' => 'null',
    'h' => "",
    'i' => [
        'j' => [
            'k' => [1, 2],
            'l' => 'mno'
        ]
    ]
]);
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test = '?a=1&b&c=true&e=false&f=null&g=null&h=&i%5Bj%5D%5Bk%5D%5B0%5D=1&i%5Bj%5D%5Bk%5D%5B1%5D=2&i%5Bj%5D%5Bl%5D=mno';
~~~